### ✅ Reload Services (Manual Trigger)
# This request manually triggers a reload of all services (RpfService, GameFileCache, etc.)
# This is useful when you've changed the GTA path and want to ensure all services are using the new path.
POST {{CodeWalkerAPI_HostAddress}}/api/reload-services
Accept: application/json

### ✅ Get Service Status
# This request retrieves the current service status including reload version and GTA path.
GET {{CodeWalkerAPI_HostAddress}}/api/service-status
Accept: application/json

### ✅ Example: Service Status with Invalid GTA Path
# When the GTA path is invalid, you'll get a response like:
# {
#   "gtaPath": "C:\\Invalid\\Path",
#   "servicesReady": false,
#   "statusMessage": "GTA V directory not found at C:\\Invalid\\Path",
#   "reloadVersion": 0,
#   "timestamp": "2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z"
# }

### ✅ Example: Service Status with Valid GTA Path
# When the GTA path is valid, you'll get a response like:
# {
#   "gtaPath": "C:\\Program Files\\Rockstar Games\\Grand Theft Auto V",
#   "servicesReady": true,
#   "statusMessage": "Services are ready",
#   "reloadVersion": 1,
#   "timestamp": "2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z"
# }

### ✅ Example: Error Response When GTA Path is Invalid
# When you try to use an endpoint with an invalid GTA path, you'll get:
# {
#   "error": "Service unavailable",
#   "message": "GTA V directory not found at C:\\Invalid\\Path. Please use /api/set-config to set a valid GTA path.",
#   "solution": "Use /api/set-config to configure a valid GTA path"
# }

### ✅ Jenkins Hash Generation (UTF8 default)
GET {{CodeWalkerAPI_HostAddress}}/api/hash/jenkins?input=prop_alien_egg_01
Accept: application/json

### ✅ Jenkins Hash Generation (ASCII encoding)
GET {{CodeWalkerAPI_HostAddress}}/api/hash/jenkins?input=prop_alien_egg_01&encoding=1
Accept: application/json

